%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Y%20Combinator-backed%20Seabound%20is%20using%20carbon-capture%20tech%20to%20tackle%20the%20shipping%20industry's%20problematic%20emissions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-planet%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-planet%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20banner-style%20logo%20for%20One%20Planet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6401033e994ec30018941bf8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22150%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Seabound%20team%20inside%20one%20of%20its%20containers%20part%20way%20through%20the%20first%20onboard%20installation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cced590b651c00193aca53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22786%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Seabound%20team%20inside%20one%20of%20its%20containers%20part%20way%20through%20the%20first%20on%20board%20installation.%3Cp%3EMark%20Potter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShipping%20produces%20about%203%25%20of%20the%20world's%20annual%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20UN's%20International%20Maritime%20Organization%20has%20set%20a%202050%20target%20for%20the%20industry%20to%20get%20to%20net%20zero.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Y%20Combinator-backed%20Seabound%20believes%20its%20on%20board%20carbon-capture%20tech%20can%20play%20a%20key%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22bold%5C%22%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fthe-blue-economy%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%220a7bc8bef72e78df4668c5761e189a61%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fthe-blue-economy%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%3EThe%20Blue%20Economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20exploring%20how%20the%20ocean%20ecosystem%20is%20being%20used%20and%20preserved%20by%20humanity.%20For%20more%20climate-action%20news%2C%20visit%20Insider's%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22bold%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-planet%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%224528c918cc46f8f24f8a2bc73f0a4548%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-planet%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-planet%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22summary_bullets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EOne%20Planet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22bold%5C%22%3E%C2%A0hub.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3Csection%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlisha%20Fredriksson%20didn't%20expect%20to%20be%20living%20on%20a%20cargo%20ship%20this%20summer.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20and%20her%20team%20are%20taking%20the%20three-month%20stints%20in%20turns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFredriksson%20is%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Seabound%2C%20a%20climate-tech%20startup%20that%20aims%20to%20lower%20the%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20produced%20by%20the%20shipping%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeabound%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20famed%20accelerator%20Y%20Combinator%2C%20has%20built%20a%20carbon-capture%20machine%20that%20can%20be%20retrofitted%20onto%20ships.%20It%20absorbs%20CO2%20from%20the%20exhaust%20gas%20and%20turns%20it%20into%20limestone%20pebbles%2C%20which%20can%20then%20be%20sold%20as%20a%20building%20material%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20avocados%20to%20clothing%2C%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fboard-of-trade-report-maritime%2Fembracing-the-ocean-a-board-of-trade-paper-web-version%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGlobal%2520maritime%2520sector%2520trends%2C-While%2520sometimes%2520overlooked%26amp%3Btext%3DApproximately%252090%2525%2520of%2520traded%2520goods%2Ccountries%2527%2520trade%2520costs%2520and%2520competitiveness.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20traded%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20carried%20on%20the%20ocean.%20As%20the%20backbone%20of%20global%20trade%2C%20shipping%20is%20responsible%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheicct.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublications%2FGlobal-shipping-GHG-emissions-2013-2015_ICCT-Report_17102017_vF.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%25%20of%20annual%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20figure%20the%20industry%20must%20slash.%20The%20UN's%20International%20Maritime%20Organization%20recently%20set%20a%20goal%20for%20the%20sector%20to%20reach%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imo.org%2Fen%2FMediaCentre%2FPressBriefings%2FPages%2FRevised-GHG-reduction-strategy-for-global-shipping-adopted-.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enet%20zero%20%26quot%3Bby%20or%20around%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%202050.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENet%20zero%20means%20to%20balance%20out%20the%20amount%20of%20emissions%20that%20are%20emitted%20with%20those%20that%20are%20removed%20from%20the%20atmosphere.%20Shipping%2C%20along%20with%20aviation%20and%20steelmaking%2C%20is%20considered%20a%20hard-to-abate%20industry%20because%20of%20its%20global%20complexities%20and%20reliance%20on%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20cost%20up%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucl.ac.uk%2Fbartlett%2Fenergy%2Fnews%2F2020%2Fjan%2Fdecarbonisation-shipping-will-take-place-land-well-sea%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520the%2520study%252C%2520the%2Ctotal%2520to%2520%25241.4%2520%252D%25201.9%2520trillion.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%241.9%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20decarbonize%20shipping%2C%20a%202020%20study%20by%20University%20College%20London%20and%20the%20environmental%20consultancy%20University%20Maritime%20Advisory%20Services%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShipping%20now%20faces%20a%20much%20harder%20challenge%20than%20it%20would%20have%20done%20had%20it%20been%20better%20at%20adapting%20and%20improving%20over%20the%20last%2010%20to%2020%20years.%20It's%20become%20very%20urgent%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stephen%20Turnock%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20engineering%20school%20at%20Southampton%20University%2C%20of%20the%20International%20Maritime%20Organization's%20latest%20guidance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20form%20of%20carbon%20capture%20will%20be%20needed%20for%20shipping%20to%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20the%20world%20spinning%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20moves%20toward%20more%20sustainable%20practices%2C%20said%20Ed%20Phillips%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20impact-investment%20fund%20Future%20Planet%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seabound%20cofounders%20Alisha%20Fredriksson%20and%20Roujia%20Wen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ccee0e0f3dff00195739d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeabound%20cofounders%20Alisha%20Fredriksson%20and%20Roujia%20Wen.%3Cp%3ESeabound%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EPiloting%20the%20technology%20on%20board%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeabound's%20end%20goal%20is%20to%20capture%2095%25%20of%20the%20carbon%20produced%20by%20a%20ship%2C%20though%20its%20current%20prototype%20captures%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20that.%C2%A0%20Having%20tested%20it%20on%20land%2C%20Seabound%20is%20now%20using%20a%20commercial%20container%20ship%20as%20its%20lab%20in%20a%20pilot%20project%20with%20the%20London-based%20shipping%20company%20Lomar%20Shipping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeabound%20moved%20the%20prototype%20from%20its%20London%20research-and-development%20facility%20to%20a%20shipyard%20in%20Yalova%2C%20Turkey%2C%20where%20it%20has%20been%20installed%20on%20a%20midsize%20ship%20that%20can%20carry%20about%203%2C200%20containers%2C%20Fredriksson%20said.%20Her%20team%20will%20take%20turns%20living%20on%20board%20to%20test%20the%20equipment%20in%20a%20real%20maritime%20environment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20equipment%20connects%20to%20the%20ship's%20exhaust%2C%20which%20flows%20through%20a%20reactor%20full%20of%20pebbles%20made%20of%20calcium-oxide%20%E2%80%93%20otherwise%20known%20as%20quicklime%2C%20limestone%20without%20the%20CO2.%20Then%20a%20mineralization%20process%20takes%20place%20where%20carbon%20dioxide%20binds%20to%20the%20pebbles%20to%20essentially%20become%20limestone.%20The%20fumes%2C%20now%20cleaner%2C%20are%20released%20through%20an%20outlet%20pipe.%20The%20limestone%20is%20temporarily%20stored%20on%20board%20and%20replaced%20with%20fresh%20calcium-oxide%20pebbles%20when%20the%20ship%20docks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup's%20opportunity%20is%20threefold%3A%20Seabound%20sells%20the%20carbon-capture%20device%20to%20ship%20owners%2C%20runs%20a%20subscription%20service%20for%20pebble%20collections%20to%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20shipowners%20to%20source%20new%20pebbles%20and%20offload%20used%20ones%2C%20and%20then%20sells%20the%20limestone%20pebbles%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20building%20material%20or%20to%20be%20sequestered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20pilot%20goes%20well%2C%20the%20team%20will%20start%20designing%20and%20testing%20a%20new%2C%20bigger%20version%20of%20the%20device%20that%20will%20be%20its%20first%20product.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20need%20some%20time%20to%20basically%20build%20that%20first%20product%2C%20so%20we%20want%20to%20move%20out%20of%20prototyping%20land%20and%20into%20actually%20having%20a%20product%20at%20a%20meaningful%20scale%20for%20our%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20Fredriksson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%20once%20we%20have%20really%20tested%20that%20on%20land%2C%20that's%20when%20we%20put%20the%20first%20full-scale%20version%20on%20a%20ship%20again.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Seabound%20team%20installing%20their%20equipment%20inside%20a%20shipping%20container%20onboard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cceda90f3dff0019573995%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20member%20of%20the%20Seabound%20team%20installing%20equipment%20inside%20a%20shipping%20container%20on%20board%20a%20cargo%20ship.%3Cp%3EAlisha%20Fredriksson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EEnergy%20and%20weight%20challenges%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShips%20usually%20get%20lighter%20through%20their%20voyage%20because%20they%20use%20up%20fuel%2C%20but%20capturing%20carbon%20means%20storing%20it%20on%20board%20in%20some%20form%2C%20which%20adds%20weight%2C%20according%20to%20Turnock.%20%26quot%3BIt%20might%20need%20a%20little%20more%20power%20to%20go%20through%20the%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20likely%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20power%2C%20he%20added%2C%20but%20it's%20compounded%20by%20the%20weight%20and%20size%20of%20the%20carbon-capture%20device%20itself.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20quite%20heavy%2C%20then%20it%20usually%20has%20to%20be%20low%20down%20on%20the%20ship%2C%20and%20then%20there%20might%20be%20difficulty%20to%20find%20the%20necessary%20volume%20to%20actually%20fit%20the%20system%20in%20without%20losing%20cargo%20capacity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShipowners%20are%20loath%20to%20lose%20cargo-carrying%20capacity%20because%20that's%20what%20makes%20them%20their%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Turnock%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20first%20pilot%2C%20Seabound%20placed%20its%20equipment%20into%20five%20shipping%20containers%20stacked%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20on%20the%20ship.%20It%20may%20require%20owners%20to%20sacrifice%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20bit%20of%20cargo%26quot%3B%20within%20the%20ship's%20max%20capacity%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bfuel%20consumption%20is%20relative%20to%20that%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20Fredriksson%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFredriksson%20added%20that%20Seabound's%20reaction%20was%20exothermic%2C%20meaning%20it%20needed%20an%20injection%20of%20heat%20to%20get%20started%20but%20then%20was%20self-sustaining.%20It%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20negligible%20energy%20consumption%20on%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20ship%20that%20Seabound%20has%20installed%20its%20pilot%20equipment%20onto.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64cceddc0b651c00193aca8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22769%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESeabound's%20pilot%20equipment%20is%20installed%20on%20this%20ship.%3Cp%3EAlisha%20Fredriksson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EDecarbonization%20requires%20all%20hands%20on%20deck%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20handful%20of%20other%20approaches%20to%20maritime%20carbon%20capture%2C%20such%20as%20using%20the%20captured%20carbon%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvaluemaritime.com%2Fvideos%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DValue%2520Maritime%2520has%2520developed%2520an%2Ccan%2520be%2520charged%2520and%2520discharged.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echarge%20a%20CO2%20battery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20overall%20it's%20a%20very%20nascent%20space.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20an%20industry%2C%20it's%20an%20emerging%20category%2C%26quot%3B%20Fredriksson%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20interesting%20is%20that%20we're%20actually%20all%20trying%20different%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20our%20responsibility%20as%20technology%20innovators%20or%20developers%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20we%20can%20work%20strategically%20or%20creatively%20within%20existing%20infrastructural%20constraints.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFredriksson%20said%20there%20were%20a%20host%20of%20creative%20ways%20being%20pursued%20to%20address%20the%20shipping%20industry's%20emissions.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20were%20all%20trying%20the%20same%20thing%2C%20it%20would%20be%20kind%20of%20silly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarbon%20capture%20aside%2C%20electric%20ships%20or%20alternative%20fuels%20are%20favored%20by%20others.%20Maersk%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20container%20carriers%20in%20the%20world%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maersk.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2022%2F11%2F16%2Fmaersk-and-carbon-sink-sign-strategic-partnership%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetting%20on%20green%20methanol%20as%20a%20fuel%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20other%20startups%20hope%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2Fpro%2Fclimate-deals%2F2023%2F06%2F01%2Facel-power-candela-x-shore-big-electric-boat-investment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectrification%20will%20take%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20focused%20more%20on%20the%20opportunity%20with%20e-methanol%2C%20with%20ammonia%2C%20hydrogen%2C%20and%20electrification%3B%20it's%20just%20avoiding%20being%20leapfrogged%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Future%20Planet%20Capital's%20Phillips.%20%26quot%3BAs%20an%20investor%20with%20a%20long-term%20view%2C%20sometimes%20backing%20a%20technology%20that%20solves%20an%20issue%20in%20the%20short-term%20can%20be%20a%20risk%20in%20itself.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20Seabound's%20tech%20looks%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20elegant%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20outsider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeapfrogging%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalmaritimeforum.org%2Fcontent%2F2023%2F04%2Fthe-shipping-industrys-fuel-choices-on-the-path-to-net-zero_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20ships%20today%20run%20on%20%3C%2Fa%3Efossil%20fuels%20and%20are%20still%20being%20ordered%2C%20Fredriksson%20said.%20Ships%20typically%20have%20a%2030-year%20lifespan%2C%20she%20added.%20The%20cost%20of%20a%20complete%20overhaul%20to%20an%20electric%20fleet%20or%20one%20that%20runs%20on%20alternative%20fuel%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bprohibitively%20expensive%26quot%3B%20while%20the%20technologies%20themselves%20are%20still%20immature%2C%20she%20added.%20At%20scale%2C%20Seabound%20intends%20to%20retrofit%20ships%20when%20they%20are%20in%20dry%20docks%20for%20routine%20maintenance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurnock%20expects%20to%20see%20a%20patchwork%20of%20technologies%20emerge.%20The%20best%20solution%20will%20depend%20on%20whether%20it's%20a%20short-distance%20ferry%20or%20a%20cargo%20ship%20sailing%20the%20high%20seas%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20there's%20a%20magic%20bullet%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20thinking%20about%20solutions%20which%20are%20overall%20good%20for%20the%20environment%20and%20make%20sense%2C%20not%20just%20ways%20of%20bookkeeping%20CO2%20so%20we're%20just%20displacing%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-backed-startup-seabound-carbon-capture-wave-shipping-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692628005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ccedf00f3dff00195739c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-backed-startup-seabound-carbon-capture-wave-shipping-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shipping%20accounts%20for%20about%203%25%20of%20global%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions.%20Seabound%20believes%20its%20tech%20can%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20helping%20it%20reach%20net%20zero.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tlockwood%40insider.com%20(Tasmin%20Lockwood)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fy-combinator-backed-startup-seabound-carbon-capture-wave-shipping-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20New%20Zealand's%20golden%20kiwis%20are%20so%20expensive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FzyNXsYR5-jZbcmOYf.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Why%20New%20Zealand's%20golden%20kiwis%20are%20so%20expensive%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGolden%20kiwis%20are%20a%20pricey%20kiwi%20variety%20known%20for%20their%20yellow%20flesh%20and%20sweet%20taste.%20Created%20by%20Zespri%2C%20New%20Zealand's%20kiwifruit%20cooperative%2C%20golden%20kiwis%20saved%20the%20island%20nation's%20local%20kiwi%20industry%20after%20a%20disease%20destroyed%20most%20of%20its%20kiwi%20orchards%20back%20in%202010.%20Despite%20costing%20nearly%20twice%20as%20much%20as%20standard%20green%20kiwis%2C%20golden%20kiwis%20have%20proven%20more%20popular%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20profitable.%20Zespri's%20SunGold%20kiwi%20strain%20is%20so%20valuable%20that%20its%20sprouts%20have%20been%20smuggled%20overseas%20and%20sold%20in%20lots%20for%2060%2C000%20New%20Zealand%20dollars.%20But%20how%20can%20a%20fruit%20be%20under%20copyright%3F%20And%20what%20makes%20this%20particular%20kiwi%20so%20expensive%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-new-zealand-golden-yellow-kiwis-are-so-expensive-china-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692627932000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-new-zealand-golden-yellow-kiwis-are-so-expensive-china-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Golden%20kiwis%20are%20a%20pricey%20kiwi%20variety%20known%20for%20tasting%20extra%20sweet.%20The%20fruit%20is%20so%20valuable%20it's%20been%20smuggled%20overseas%20and%20sold%20for%20NZ%2460%2C000.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ikim%40insider.com%20(Irene%20Anna%20Kim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-new-zealand-golden-yellow-kiwis-are-so-expensive-china-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Union%20Home%20Ministry%20Tops%20Corruption%20Complaints%2C%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Report%20Finds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F21165755%2FHome-Ministry-PTI9_19_2019_000103B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20(CVC)%2C%20in%20its%20annual%20report%2C%20has%20said%20that%20it%20has%20received%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20corruption%20complaints%20relating%20to%20officers%20and%20employees%20of%20the%20Union%20ministry%20for%20home%20affairs%20(MHA)%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20it%20had%20received%20a%20total%20of%201%2C15%2C203%20complaints%20till%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20across%20all%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2085%2C437%20complaints%20had%20been%20disposed%2C%2029%2C766%20were%20pending%2C%20and%2022%2C034%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20number%20of%20complaints%20related%20to%20MHA%20(46%2C643)%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Railways%20(10%2C580)%20and%20Banks%20(8%2C129).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CVC%20is%20the%20apex%20agency%20overseeing%20and%20supervising%20the%20vigilance%20administration%20of%20the%20organisations%20owned%20or%20controlled%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20covered%20under%20the%20advisory%20jurisdiction%20of%20the%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20meant%20to%20tackle%20corruption%20and%20make%20the%20administrative%20system%20transparent%20and%20objective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHighest%20corruption%20complaints%20in%20MHA%2C%20Railways%2C%20and%20Banking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20of%2046%2C643%20received%20against%20officers%20and%20employees%20of%20the%20MHA%2C%2023%2C919%20were%20disposed%20of%3B%2022%2C724%20were%20pending%20and%2019%2C198%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20of%20the%2010%2C580%20complaints%20it%20had%20received%20relating%20to%20Railways%2C%209%2C663%20were%20disposed%20of%2C%20917%20were%20pending%20and%20nine%20were%20pending%20for%20over%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%208%2C129%20complaints%20against%20employees%20and%20officers%20of%20Banks%2C%207%2C762%20were%20disposed%20of%2C%20367%20were%20pending%20and%2078%20were%20pending%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20there%20were%207%2C370%20complaints%20against%20employees%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2C%206%2C804%20were%20disposed%20of%20and%20566%20were%20pending%2C%20including%2018%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeviations%20from%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20there%20were%2027%20cases%20of%20deviation%20from%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20across%2016%20departments%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20included-Ministry%20of%20Railways%20(7)%2C%20Bharat%20Sanchar%20Nigam%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20V.O%20Chidambaranar%20Port%20Authority%20(1)%2C%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(2)%2C%20New%20India%20Assurance%20Company%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20Industrial%20Development%20Bank%20of%20India%20(1)%2C%20Small%20Industries%20Development%20Bank%20of%20India%20(1)%2C%20Bharat%20Coking%20Coal%20Ltd%20(1)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Coal%20(2)%2C%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Ltd%20(2)%2C%20Bird%20Group%20of%20Companies%20(1)%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Textiles%20(1)%2C%20NBCC%20(India)%20Ltd%20(3)%2C%20Delhi%20State%20Industrial%20and%20Infrastructure%20Development%20Corporation%20(1)%2C%20Delhi%20Jal%20Board%20(1)%2C%20and%20Delhi%20Transco%20Ltd%20(1).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhenever%20the%20Ministry%2FDepartment%20proposes%20to%20differ%20from%20or%20not%20to%20accept%20any%20advice%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20a%20procedure%20has%20been%20laid%20down%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20%26amp%3B%20Administrative%20Reforms%2C%20which%20prescribes%20that%20in%20those%20cases%20of%20officers%20for%20whom%20the%20Appointing%20Authority%20is%20the%20President%2C%20(orders%20are%20required%20to%20be%20issued%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20President)%2C%20a%20reference%20is%20to%20be%20made%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20%26amp%3B%20Training%20(DOPT)%20before%20the%20Ministry%2FDepartment%20finally%20decides%20such%20cases%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNon-acceptance%20of%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%20vitiates%20the%20vigilance%20process%20and%20weakens%20the%20impartiality%20of%20the%20vigilance%20administration.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20cases%20of%20deviation%20from%20a%20prescribed%20procedure%20or%20non-acceptance%20of%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20advice%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20major%20instances%20of%20deviation%20cases%20from%20the%20CVC%E2%80%99s%20advice%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Railways%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20working%20as%20chief%20workshop%20manager%20(CWM)%2C%20an%20officer%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20committing%20gross%20misconduct%20by%20introducing%20the%20then%20(senior%20section%20engineer%20(SSE))%20as%20his%20friend%20to%20the%20supplier%20and%20demanding%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2025%2C000%20through%20the%20then%20SSE%20for%20passing%20the%20supplier%E2%80%99s%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20CVC%20had%20advised%20imposition%20of%20a%20major%20penalty%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20Railway%20Board%20decided%20to%20exonerate%20him%20which%20the%20commission%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajor%20deviation%E2%80%9D%20from%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20instance%2C%20another%20senior%20section%20engineer%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20processing%20payment%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20fake%20inspection%20certificate.%20The%20officer%20was%20also%20exonerated%20in%20a%20deviation%20from%20the%20CVC%E2%80%99s%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20instance%2C%20a%20senior%20divisional%20engineer%20failed%20to%20investigate%20complaints%20received%20from%20an%20additional%20divisional%20railway%20manager%20(ADRM)%20and%20failed%20to%20exercise%20due%20diligence%20in%20the%20scrutiny%20of%20credential%20documents%20of%20a%20firm.%20This%20resulted%20in%20award%20of%20contract%20to%20a%20firm%20on%20fake%2Fforged%20credential%20papers.%20While%20the%20Commission%20adviced%20major%20penalty%2C%20only%20a%20minor%20penalty%20was%20imposed%20by%20the%20Railway%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%20Jal%20Board%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIrregularities%20were%20found%20in%20the%20tendering%20process%20for%20the%20award%20of%20work%20of%20construction%20of%2050-kilo%20litres%20per%20day%20sewage%20treatment%20plant%20(STP)%20and%20other%20associated%20works%20on%20a%20Design-Build%20Operate%20basis%20at%20Raj%20Niwas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Commission%20had%20advised%20imposing%20a%20major%20penalty%2C%20the%20Disciplinary%20Authority%20exonerated%20the%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Textile%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAn%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Fashion%20Technology%20(NIFT)%20Bhubaneshwar%20was%20found%20responsible%20for%20gross%20violation%20in%20tender%20evaluation%20and%20for%20proposing%20to%20release%20part%20payment%20directly%20to%20the%20individual%20and%20not%20to%20the%20firm%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20work%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20major%20penalty%20was%20imposed%20by%20the%20Disciplinary%20Authority%2C%20the%20Appellate%20Authority%20later%20exonerated%20the%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinistry%20of%20Coal%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEastern%20Coalfields%20Ltd%20(ECL)%20awarded%20contracts%20for%20hiring%20Heavy%20Earth%20Moving%20Machinery%20(HEMM)%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20overburden%2C%20extraction%2C%20and%20removal%20of%20coal%20from%20Mohanpur%2C%20OCP%20patch%20of%20Salanpur%20Area%20and%20Jambad%20Open%20Cast%20Project%20(OCP)%20Kajora%20Area.%20The%20contracts%20were%20foreclosed%20and%20were%20awarded%20at%20higher%20rates%20in%20retendering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20two%20officers%20were%20exonerated%20in%20a%20major%20deviation%20from%20its%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%2C%20minor%20penalties%20and%20exonerations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20annual%20reports%20of%20chief%20vigilance%20officers%20(CVOs)%20of%20organisations%20%E2%80%93%20major%20penalty%20proceedings%20were%20initiated%20in%206%2C501%20cases%20for%20all%20categories%20of%20officers%20dealt%20with%20by%20the%20CVO.%20This%20resulted%20in%20the%20imposition%20of%20major%20penalties%20in%205%2C298%20cases%20and%20minor%20penalties%20or%20warnings%20in%20552%20cases.%20651%20cases%20resulted%20in%20exoneration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinor%20penalty%20proceedings%20were%20initiated%20in%2013%2C661%20cases%20in%20which%20minor%20penalties%20or%20warnings%20were%20issued%20in%2011%2C751%20cases%20and%203%2C752%20ca