88w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669008%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIran%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20Mohammad%20Mosaddegh%20was%20overthrown%20by%20an%20Anglo-US%20coup%20in%201953.%20Photo%3A%20Wikipedia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%201951%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20parliament%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Flibrary%2Fworld%2Fmideast%2F032551iran-oil-vote.html%5C%22%3Evoted%20to%20proceed%20with%20nationalisation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20caused%20consternation%20in%20the%20west%20%E2%80%93%20most%20notably%20in%20Britain%2C%20where%20the%20prospect%20of%20nationalisation%20was%20seen%20as%20potentially%20hugely%20damaging%20to%20the%20economy.%20Furthermore%2C%20it%20would%20have%20undermined%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Plotting%20to%20depose%20Mosaddegh%20began%20in%20earnest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20event%2C%20the%20coup%20%E2%80%93%20named%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2017%2F06%2F20%2F64-years-later-cia-finally-releases-details-of-iranian-coup-iran-tehran-oil%2F%5C%22%3EOperation%20Ajax%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20was%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20the%20CIA%20and%20MI6.%20The%20shah%2C%20Mohammad%20Reza%20Pahlavi%2C%20who%20had%20recently%20fled%20the%20country%20after%20an%20earlier%20plot%20to%20remove%20Mossadegh%20had%20failed%2C%20returned%20to%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20short%20period%2C%20he%20had%20tightened%20his%20grip%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20security%20services%20and%20imposed%20a%20dictatorial%20regime%20which%20ruled%20through%20brutality%20and%20fear.%20Pahlavi%20banned%20all%20opposition%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20many%20of%20the%20activists%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20movement%20for%20nationalisation%20of%20oil%20were%20arrested%20or%20fled%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20by%20fear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C