agement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbank-of-baroda-explains-why-it-withdrew-sunny-deols-bungalow-auction-notice-4315919%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20Made%20In%20Heaven's%20Dalit%20Wedding%20Is%20More%20Radical%20Than%20You%20Think%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWith%20much%20talked%20about%20episode%205%20of%20%3Cem%3EMade%20in%20Heaven%202%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Neeraj%20Ghaywan%20redefines%20the%20discourse%20on%20caste%20in%20mainstream%20Hindi%20filmmaking.%20While%20many%20films%20dealing%20with%20the%20theme%20of%20caste%20prejudices%20have%20been%20made%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20approach%20caste%20as%20a%20system%20of%20discrimination%20and%20place%20their%20hopes%20in%20modernity%20and%20a%20mirage%20of%20a%20casteless%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20episode%20is%20radical%20because%20it%20questions%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20a%20casteless%20society%2C%20as%20it%20demands%20adherence%20to%20upper-caste%20norms%20and%20the%20erasure%20of%20the%20Dalit%20past.%20Instead%20of%20advocating%20Dalits%20joining%20the%20mainstream%20by%20forgetting%20their%20past%2C%20it%20asks%20for%20the%20reclamation%20of%20history%20and%20its%20celebration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22u3emota4%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fu3emota4_embed1_625x300_21_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%202%3A%20The%20Heart%20Skipped%20A%20Beat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeeraj%20Ghaywan%20has%20consistently%20made%20films%20on%20Dalit%20themes%2C%20and%20with%20his%20career%2C%20the%20discourse%20around%20Dalit%20issues%20has%20also%20evolved.%20Tracing%20his%20cinematic%20work%2C%20one%20can%20also%20see%20a%20journey%20of%20the%20theme%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2015)%2C%20Ghaywan's%20debut%20film%2C%20traces%20the%20journey%20of%20a%20Dalit%20boy%20and%20an%20upper%20caste%20girl.%20Both%20of%20them%20escape%20an%20oppressive%20society%20that%20thrives%20on%20the%20ideas%20of%20caste%20and%20honour.%20Their%20employment%20with%20the%20Railways%2C%20the%20vehicle%20of%20modernity%2C%20brings%20them%20to%20Allahabad%20(now%2C%20Prayagraj)%2C%20the%20city%20of%20confluence%2C%20and%20the%20film%20ends%20on%20a%20feel-good%20note%20where%20caste%20seems%20to%20have%20gotten%20irrelevant%20because%20none%20of%20the%20characters%20practises%20their%20caste-based%20occupations.%20As%20migrant%20workers%20of%20modernity%2C%20they%20are%20in%20the%20same%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ending%20of%20Masaan%20is%20feelgood%20because%20it%20assumes%20that%20once%20people%20from%20different%20castes%20get%20employed%20in%20modern%20workplaces%20such%20as%20railways%2C%20caste-based%20prejudices%20will%20cease%20to%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhaywan%20revisits%20this%20assumption%20in%20his%20short%2C%20%3Cem%3EGeeli%20Puchi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Part%20of%20the%202021%20Netflix%20anthology%20%3Cem%3EAjeeb%20Daastaan%3C%2Fem%3Es).%20Here%2C%20two%20women%20work%20in%20a%20modern%20factory%2C%20but%20still%2C%20the%20Dalit%20woman%20faces%20discrimination%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20career%20advancement.%20Though%20the%20film%20intricately%20tells%20the%20stories%20of%20the%20central%20characters%2C%20Ghaywan%20scrutinises%20his%20earlier%20assumption%20and%20offers%20a%20new%20finding.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20upper%20castes%20own%20the%20means%20of%20production%2C%20the%20Dalit%20workers%20will%20continue%20to%20face%20discrimination%20unless%20they%20learn%20the%20shrewdness%20of%20the%20upper%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much%20talked%20about%20fifth%20episode%20of%20%3Cem%3EMade%20in%20Heaven%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20takes%20us%20into%20the%20future%20and%20scrutinises%20the%20assumption%20that%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20made%2C%20just%20that%20genders%20are%20reversed%2C%20and%20the%20class%20difference%20has%20narrowed.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20casteless%20society%20of%20the%20USA%2C%20a%20Dalit%20woman%20and%20an%20upper-caste%20man%20fall%20in%20love%20and%20decide%20to%20get%20married.%20So%20far%2C%20so%20good%2C%20as%20there%20are%20no%20raised%20eyebrows%20of%20parents%2C%20no%20elopement%20or%20honour%20killing.%20Everything%20goes%20without%20a%20glitch%20until%20the%20ritual%20of%20marriage%20is%20discussed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dalit%20girl%20doesn't%20want%20a%20Brahmanical%20ritualistic%20marriage%2C%20and%20the%20man%20is%20okay%20with%20it%2C%20but%20his%20family%20isn't.%20They%20want%20a%20brief%20ritual%20of%20%3Cem%3Ephera%3C%2Fem%3Es%20after%20the%20registration%20of%20the%20marriage.%20When%20the%20girl%20asserts%20and%20wants%20to%20have%20a%20Dalit%20Buddhist%20wedding%20to%20follow%20the%20%3Cem%3Ephera%3C%2Fem%3Es%2C%20the%20family%20tries%20many%20tricks%20to%20get%20her%20to%20drop%20the%20idea.%20Even%20worse%2C%20her%20groom-to-be%20fails%20to%20empathise%20with%20her.%20The%20episode%20ends%20with%20the%20upper%20caste%20man's%20realisation%20of%20his%20family's%20hidden%20prejudices%20against%20the%20girl's%20assertion%20of%20her%20identity.%20And%20finally%2C%20Ghaywan%20shows%20us%20what%20a%20Dalit%20wedding%20could%20look%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22dlvid0js%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fdlvid0js_embed_625x300_21_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EMade%20In%20Heaven%202%3A%20The%20Heart%20Skipped%20A%20Beat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20episode%20re-examines%20some%20of%20the%20assumptions%20on%20which%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20ends.%20Will%20caste%20still%20matter%20in%20a%20casteless%20society%3F%20The%20answer%20that%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20brings%20forth%20is%3A%20%26quot%3Bmaybe%26quot%3B.%20But%2C%20Ghaywan%20revises%20the%20answer%20in%20the%20episode%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20caste%20still%20matters%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20rituals%20of%20marriage%20if%20not%20marriage%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20equality%20is%20revisited%2C%20too.%20Will%20caste%20cease%20to%20matter%20if%20people%20take%20up%20modern%20professions%3F%20And%2C%20when%20the%20economic%20class%20difference%20narrows%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20that%20the%20episode%20presents%20is%20very%20different%20from%20%3Cem%3EMasaan%3C%2Fem%3E's.%20Episode%205%20is%20politically%20more%20complex%20as%20it%20shows%20how%20problematic%20slogans%20such%20as%20bringing%20Dalits%20into%20the%20mainstream%20is.%20It%20means%20acceptance%20only%20as%20long%20as%20Dalits%20live%20in%20denial%20of%20their%20past%20and%20assume%20the%20codes%20of%20upper%20castes.%20However%2C%20when%20a%20Dalit%20person%20asserts%20her%20identity%20and%20demands%20a%20celebration%20of%20her%20heritage%2C%20it%20makes%20the%20upper%20caste%20household%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20episode%20is%20important%20because%20it%20proclaims%20a%20significant%20departure%20in%20Dalit%20discourse%20in%20mainstream%20Hindi%20filmmaking%2C%20from%20the%20portrayal%20of%20oppression%20to%20the%20assertion%20of%20identity.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20catch%20that%20the%20episode%20captures%20beautifully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20bride-to-be%20asserts%20her%20Dalit%20identity%20unapologetically%2C%20her%20family%2C%20particularly%20her%20younger%20brother%2C%20holds%20it%20against%20her.%20Why%3F%20He%20says%20he%20won't%20like%20being%20identified%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bquota%20student%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20college.%20So%2C%20the%20assertion%20is%20a%20path%20fraught%20with%20risks%2C%20like%20it%20is%20for%20the%20brother%20in%20a%20caste-ridden%20society%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20episode%2C%20Ghaywan%20busts%20the%20myth%20of%20the%20mainstream%20and%20defines%20it%20as%20an%20idea%20of%20cultural%20subjugation.%20Instead%20of%20seeking%20admission%20into%20the%20mainstream%20by%20accepting%20Brahmanical%20rituals%2C%20Ghaywan%20advocates%20the%20need%20for%20new%20symbols%20and%20new%20rituals.%20And%2C%20who%20better%20to%20turn%20to%20for%20that%20than%20Buddha%20and%20Ambedkar%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghaywan%20and%20the%20writers%20of%20the%20show%20Alankrita%20Shrivastava%2C%20Zoya%20Akhtar%2C%20Reema%20Kagti%20and%20additional%20writer%20Rahul%20Nair%20deserve%20all%20the%20credit%20for%20redefining%20the%20Dalit%20discourse%20into%20the%20mainstream%2C%20it's%20somewhat%20tragic%20that%20creators%20resorted%20to%20cold%20legality%20after%20Yashica%20Dutt%20(%3Cem%3EComing%20Out%20as%20Dalit%3A%20A%20Memoir%3C%2Fem%3E)%20demanded%20credit%20in%20the%20episode%20claiming%20that%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Dalit%20girl's%20character%20is%20based%20on%20her.%20Strangely%2C%20Ghaywan%20had%20even%20acknowledged%20her%20as%20an%20inspiration%20for%20the%20character%20(particularly%20the%20interview%20scene)%20before%20posting%20her%20demand's%20rebuttal%20on%20Instagram.%20One%20would%20have%20expected%20more%20grace%20and%20empathy%20from%20the%20creators%20of%20a%20show%20which%20successfully%20raises%20the%20issues%20of%20discrimination.%20Would%20it%20have%20hurt%20to%20acknowledge%20her%20contribution%20on%20the%20screen%20if%20they%20already%20did%20so%20on%20social%20media%3F%20Isn't%20the%20controversy%20essentially%20the%20same%20denial%20the%20episode%20claims%20to%20expose%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bikas%20Mishra%20is%20an%20award-winning%20writer-director%20based%20in%20Mumbai)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692617520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fi7g413f4_bikas240_120x90_03_July_23.jpg%3Fver-20230818.04%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fopinion-why-made-in-heavens-dalit-wedding-is-more-radical-than-you-think-4316016%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Instead%20of%20seeking%20admission%20into%20the%20mainstream%20by%20accepting%20Brahmanical%20rituals%2C%20Ghaywan%20advocates%20the%20need%20for%20new%20symbols%20and%20new%20rituals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fopinion-why-made-in-heavens-dalit-wedding-is-more-radical-than-you-think-4316016%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fopinion-why-made-in-heavens-dalit-wedding-is-more-radical-than-you-think-4316016%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fopinion-why-made-in-heavens-dalit-wedding-is-more-radical-than-you-think-4316016%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine's%20use%20of%20imprecise%20cluster%20bombs%20is%20making%20Russian%20'very%20scared%20to%20go%20on%20assault'%2C%20says%20frontline%20soldier%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22cluster%20bomb%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e335acbd98a600197ab173%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20walks%20past%20an%20unexploded%20tail%20section%20of%20a%20300mm%20rocket%20which%20appear%20to%20contained%20cluster%20bombs%2C%20fired%20at%20eastern%20Ukraine%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3EANATOLII%20STEPANOV%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUkraine's%20use%20of%20US%20cluster%20bombs%20is%20deterring%20Russian%20attacks%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20decision%20to%20provide%20Ukraine%20with%20the%20weapon%20was%20controversial.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20weapons%20disperse%20bombs%20and%20shrapnel%20over%20a%20wide%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20says%20that%20controversial%20cluster%20munitions%20supplied%20by%20the%20US%20are%20proving%20important%20for%20stopping%20Russian%20attacks%20on%20its%20positions%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fukraine-cluster-bombs-biden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20decision%20to%20send%20the%20weapons%20to%20Ukraine%20in%20July%20attracted%20criticism%2C%20with%20allies%20including%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20Canada%20expressing%20concern%20over%20potential%20civilian%20casualties.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weapons%20differ%20from%20normal%20munitions%2C%20which%20land%20and%20create%20a%20single%20explosion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECluster%20munitions%20break%20apart%20above%20their%20target%2C%20dispersing%20large%20numbers%20of%20small%20bombs%20over%20a%20wide%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20smaller%20bombs%20often%20don't%20detonate%20properly%2C%20and%20can%20lie%20unexploded%20for%20years%2C%20posing%20a%20lasting%20threat%20to%20local%20populations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20officials%20told%20the%20Post%20that%20the%20weapons%20were%20having%20an%20important%20impact%20on%20the%20front%20line%2C%20helping%20to%20slow%20and%20deter%20Russian%20attacks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20benefit%20is%20that%20the%20enemy%20is%20now%20very%20scared%20to%20go%20on%20assault%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stanislav%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20military%20official%20whom%20The%20Post%20identified%20only%20by%20his%20call%20sign%20for%20security%20reasons.%20%26quot%3BThey%20even%20recognize%20the%20cluster%20bombs%20by%20the%20whistle%20they%20make%20when%20headed%20their%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Stanislav%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Biden%20agreed%20to%20Ukrainian%20requests%20for%20the%20weapons%2C%20analysts%20said%20their%20main%20use%20would%20be%20to%20help%20Ukraine%20break%20through%20Russia's%20formidable%20defenses%20as%20part%20of%20its%20counteroffensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20reported%20that%20they%20have%20been%20useful%20defensively%20too.%20While%20Ukraine%20is%20attacking%2C%20Russian%20troops%20can%20shelter%20in%20their%20trenches%20and%20avoid%20much%20of%20the%20damage.%20But%20if%20the%20Russians%20are%20advancing%20over%20open%20ground%2C%20then%20the%20weapons%20can%20be%20devastating.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20said%20the%20offensive%20use%20of%20the%20cluster%20munitions%20has%20been%20in%20pinning%20down%20Russian%20troops%2C%20meaning%20they%20stay%20sheltering%20as%20Ukraine%20advances.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fukraine-apparent-russian-cluster-munition-attack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Rand%20think%20tank%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20the%20munitions%20were%20especially%20useful%20given%20that%20Ukraine's%20regular%20artillery%20stocks%20were%20badly%20depleted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20100%20countries%20are%20signatories%20to%20the%20the%20Convention%20on%20Cluster%20Munitions%2C%20which%20bans%20the%20use%20and%20stockpiling%20of%20the%20weapon.%20US%20allies%20like%20the%20UK%2C%20Germany%20and%20France%20have%20agreed%20not%20the%20use%20them%2C%20but%20the%20US%2C%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20are%20not%20signatories%20of%20the%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20have%20used%20the%20munitions%20during%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Fukraine-apparent-russian-cluster-munition-attack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20Russia%20accused%20of%20using%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20weapons%20in%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-cluster-bomb-use-deters-russian-attacks-report-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692617462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e335b9b698ac0019dde9a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-cluster-bomb-use-deters-russian-attacks-report-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20issuing%20US%20cluster%20bombs%20to%20devastate%20the%20Russian%20military%2C%20amid%20ongoing%20controversy%20over%20their%20use.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A23%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-cluster-bomb-use-deters-russian-attacks-report-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Godavari%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20Here%E2%80%99%3A%20From%20Intimacy%20to%20Distance%20for%20the%20Adivasi%20Community%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21153122%2Fimage-1239.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20another%20International%20Day%20of%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Indigenous%20Peoples%20went%20by%20on%20August%209.%20That%20day%2C%20in%20one%20part%20of%20rural%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20(R%26amp%3BR%20colony%2C%20ASR%20district)%2C%20Kondareddis%20and%20few%20other%20adivasi%20communities%20took%20out%20a%20procession%20under%20the%20aegis%20of%20the%20Agency%20Girijana%20Sangham.%20This%20procession%2C%20which%20I%20saw%20in%20photographs%2C%20was%20different%20from%20their%20long%20march%20I%E2%80%99d%20witnessed%20in%20person%20in%202016%2C%20at%20Kondamodalu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20procession%20was%20an%20amazing%20blend%20of%20colours%3A%20golden%20sands%2C%20red%20flags%20amid%20lush%20green%20fields%2C%20with%20the%20Papikonda%20hills%20serving%20its%20almost%20theatrical%20backdrop%2C%20through%20the%20ancient%20and%20almost%20linear%20path%20of%20historic%20adivasi%20revolts%20and%20resistance%20since%20colonial%20times%20onwards.%20The%20Kondareddis%20and%20other%20adivasis%20of%20that%20march%20had%20shouted%20the%20slogans%3A%20%3Cem%3Ejohaar%20amara%20veerula%20ki%2C%20Bhoomi%20kosam%2C%20vimukti%20kosam%20poraadali%20%3C%2Fem%3E(salute%20the%20martyrs%2C%20let%20us%20fight%20for%20land%20and%20freedom%2Fautonomy)%2C%20while%20the%20August%209%20procession%20demanded%20corporates%20to%20quit%20agriculture%20and%20forests.%20Things%20have%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152459%2Fimage-1235.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22940%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152459%2Fimage-1235.png%20793w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152459%2Fimage-1235-300x164.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668989%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22513%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20long%20march%20in%20Kondamodalu.%20Photo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERespecting%20the%20idea%20behind%20designating%20a%20day%20for%20indigenous%20peoples%2C%20one%20remembers%20a%20space%20and%20its%20people%2C%20marginalised%20in%20the%20mainstream%20development%20discourse%2C%20screaming%20%E2%80%98Hindutva%E2%80%99.%20You%20could%20see%20it%20reflected%20in%20the%20symbols%20entering%20the%20physical%20space%20of%20the%20parliament%20building%3A%20a%20%E2%80%98Sengol%E2%80%99%20so%20far%20removed%20from%20the%20history%20and%20culture%20of%20the%20indigenous%20peoples%20of%20the%20country.%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20equally%20patronising%20is%20that%20the%20symbol%20comes%20from%20a%20Tamil%20historical%20context%20(of%20a%20regime)%2C%20not%20necessarily%20benevolent%20to%20communities%20such%20as%20the%20Tamil%20Jainas%20or%20Buddhists%20of%20that%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20apt%2C%20then%2C%20to%20wonder%20as%20to%20where%20we%20are%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20indigenous%20peoples.%20Globally%2C%20do%20nations%20across%20the%20world%20represent%20them%20in%20fairness%2C%20truth%2C%20and%20equality%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EIkkada%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EAkkada%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Intimacy%20and%20Distance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntimacy%20and%20distance%20seem%20to%20be%20two%20idioms%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98posts%E2%80%99%2C%20within%20which%20the%20adivasi%20life%20histories%20could%20be%20written.%20And%20then%2C%20there%20are%20two%20other%20metaphors%3A%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%20%3C%2Fem%3E(here%20and%20there).%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Kondamodalu%20adivasis%2C%20intimacy%20and%20belonging%20happened%20(in%20the%20%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20the%20world%20of%20the%20forests%20on%20hilly%20ranges%2C%20amid%20which%20were%20their%20homes%2C%20at%20one%20end%2C%20and%20a%20river%20(Godavari)%20at%20the%20other%2C%20towards%20%3Cem%3Ewhom%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20walked%20a%20few%20kilometres%20each%20day%3A%20to%20cross-over%20(to%20the%20other%20villages%2C%20or%20to%20work)%2C%20or%20to%20bathe%20and%20wash%20in%2C%20and%20generally%2C%20to%20watch%20as%20the%20moon%20rose%20and%20the%20sun%20set.%20Or%2C%20even%20simpler%20still%2C%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20the%20fishermen%2C%20whose%20intimacy%20belonged%20in%20the%20river%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKondamodalu%20panchayat%2C%20under%20a%20vast%20open%20sky%2C%20was%20an%20expansive%20space%20with%20large%20homesteads%20snugly%20situated%20under%20the%20shades%20of%20wide%20Tamarind%20trees%20(with%20their%20own%20botanical%20and%20cultural%20histories%20dating%20back%20several%20centuries)%2C%20within%20walking%20distance%20from%20those%20equally%20ancient%20%3Cem%3EIppa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Bassia%20latifolia%20%2F%20Madhuca%20indica)%20and%20%3Cem%3Etadi%20chettu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Toddy).%20Theirs%20truly%20became%20the%20last%20post%20of%20resistance%20to%20the%20Polavaram%20dam%20(I%20wish%20I%20had%20not%20titled%20my%20piece%20thus%2C%20those%20many%20years%20ago)%2C%20until%20they%20could%20hold%20no%20longer.%20Today%2C%20they%20have%20accepted%20forced%20distance%2C%20from%20all%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20eve%20of%20August%209%20(this%20year)%2C%20I%20received%20a%20most%20unexpected%20phone%20call%2C%20and%20the%20chance%20to%20listen%20in%2C%20all%20over%20again%2C%20to%20the%20Kondamodalu%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijaya%20(of%20Kathanapally)%20told%20me%20the%20difference%20between%20then%20and%20now%2C%20between%20home%20and%20a%20house%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eakkada%20adanta%20manadi%20kada%3F%20Mana%2C%20ane%20undedi%2C%20ekkadaina%20vellocchu%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5BThere%2C%20all%20of%20it%20was%20%3Cem%3Eours%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20it%3F%20It%20was%20the%20sense%20of%20%3Cem%3Eour(s)%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewe%20could%20go%20anywhere%20(with%20the%20feeling%20that%20we%20stroll%20around%20in%20our%20space).%E2%80%9D%20Today%2C%20she%20says%2C%20they%20are%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20cemented%20houses%20on%20approximately%202.5-4%20cents%20of%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152715%2Fimage-1236.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22612%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152715%2Fimage-1236.png%20612w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152715%2Fimage-1236-204x300.png%20204w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668991%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22902%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVijaya%20and%20others.%20Photo%3A%20R.%20Umamaheshwari%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGodavari%20had%20given%20me%20many%20metaphors%20and%20idioms%20over%20the%20years.%20What%20I%20used%20to%20see%20as%20simply%20%E2%80%98terms%E2%80%99%20became%20words%20laden%20with%20meaning%2C%20reflecting%20the%20human-non-human%20connect%2C%20or%20the%20way%20nature%20was%20perceived%2C%20signifying%20the%20centrality%20of%20a%20phenomenon%2C%20or%20form%20of%20life%2C%20to%20the%20community%20in%20their%20everyday%20contexts.%20Phrases%2C%20proverbs%2C%20ways%20of%20addressing%20a%20form%20or%20phenomenon%20revealed%20connections%2C%20which%20had%20otherwise%20become%20forced%20binaries%20within%20modernity%20and%20colonialism%2C%20world%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20times%2C%20after%20centuries%20of%20struggle%2C%20the%20Maoris%20were%20able%20to%20convince%20the%20governance%20systems%20that%20Wanghnui%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20a%20river%2C%20but%20a%20person%2C%20their%20ancestor%3B%20but%20what%20is%20more%2C%20that%20ancestor%20could%20have%20legal%20rights%2C%20just%20any%20human.%20That%20Godavari%20%3Cem%3Ecame%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Estayed%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Ewent%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eretreated%3C%2Fem%3E%20(or%20%3Cem%3Eshe%20will%20not%20come%20this%20time%3C%2Fem%3E)%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Eocchindi%2F%20occhinadi%2C%20untundi%20%2F%20untadi%2C%20potundi%20%2F%20potadi%2C%20teesindi%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20may%20have%20had%20the%20same%20idea%20of%20a%20person%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20language%2C%20but%20the%20river%20is%20still%20ruled%20by%20the%20colonial%20legacy%20of%20power%20and%20control%2C%20to%20be%20dammed%20and%20commodified%20purposefully%20and%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20Kondareddis%20fields%20inundated%20by%20%E2%80%98Godavari%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20political%20flooding%20(of%20waters%2C%20and%20not%20the%20natural%20coming%20of%20Godavari)%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%2042.5%20ft%20Polavaram%20Coffer%20dam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijaya%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwater%20is%20not%20receding%20like%20it%20did%20earlier.%20Godavari%20would%20come%20around%20August%2015%2C%20and%20recede%20within%20two%20weeks%3B%20now%20the%20water%20stays%20longer%20in%20the%20fields.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDigressing%20here%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20roadways%20have%20eaten%20into%20rivers%20and%20mountains%20and%20the%20present%20destruction%20is%20yet%20another%20example%20of%20the%20politics%20of%20deluge.%20It%20is%20fascinating%20to%20look%20at%20how%20ritualistic%20intimacy%20with%20rivers%20during%20certain%20religious%20occasions%20sits%20uncomfortably%20(or%20comfortably%2C%20who%20is%20to%20tell%3F)%20with%20the%20distance%20built%20through%20the%20political%20economy%20of%20networks%20and%20highways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20first%20saw%20Kondareddi%20Madi%20Muttemma%20of%20Kokkarigudem%20in%202006%20(when%20I%20did%20not%20know%20her%20name)%20at%20the%20Panchayat%20office%2C%20in%20pouring%20rain%20(during%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fgodavari-flood-ap-25-lakh-cusecs-mark-8033923%2F%5C%22%3E%202006%20Godavari%3C%2Fa%3E)%3B%20she%20had%20the%20loudest%20voice%20as%20she%20questioned%20government%20officials%20on%20relief%20material%20not%20reaching%20them.%20In%202009%2C%20I%20got%20to%20interview%20her.%20She%20was%20then%20the%20MPTC%20(member%20of%20the%20Mandal%20Parishat%20Territorial%20Council)%20of%20Kondamodalu.%20And%20it%20was%20her%20usage%20of%20the%20words%2C%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20made%20me%20see%20her%20wisdom%20about%20the%20true%20meaning%20of%20dispossession.%20There%20was%20a%20sense%20of%20home%20in%20that%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20conversation%2C%20I%20would%20listen%20more%20carefully%20to%20these%20two%20words%2C%20realising%20that%20women%20used%20them%20more%20often%20than%20men%20did.%20%3Cem%3EIkkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereflected%20the%20intimacy%20(thereby%20belonging%20in%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebeing%20in%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20distance%20(via%20a%20forced%20%3Cem%3Ebecoming%3C%2Fem%3E%20through%20governance%20and%20power)%3B%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Emade%20%E2%80%98oustees%E2%80%99%20of%20a%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20a%20village%20becomes%20the%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20the%20colony.%20The%20Kondareddis%20are%20now%20living%20in%20the%20R%26amp%3BR%20colony%2C%20which%20they%20have%20named%20(from%20a%20sense%20of%20nostalgia%20and%20pain)%2C%20%3Cem%3EKottha%20(new)%20Kondamodalu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20And%20hence%2C%20now%20%3Cem%3EPatha%20Kondamodalu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20was%20once%20their%20intimate%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20now%20become%20the%20distant%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Evia%20their%20nemesis%2C%20the%20Polavaram%20dam.%20So%20now%20you%20have%20to%20understand%20in%20a%20different%20sense%20when%20Muttemma%20or%20Vijaya%20or%20others%20tell%20you%20that%20they%20cannot%20go%20to%20Kondamodalu%20(the%20original)%20because%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eippudu%20akkada%20Godavari%20unthandi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(now%20there%20is%20Godavari%20there)%3B%20by%20this%2C%20they%20mean%20the%20political%20waters%20from%20a%20political%20project%2C%20and%20not%20the%20natural%20coming%20of%20a%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20Muttemma%20had%20told%20me%20in%20the%20past%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20locality%2C%20since%20this%20is%20an%20agency%20area%2C%20we%20have%20access%20to%20everything%2C%20except%20for%20salt%2C%20which%20we%20purchase%20at%20the%20Santa%20fair.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20plains%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20need%20to%20purchase%20everything%2C%20including%20vegetables%20and%20fruits.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20adivasis%20of%20the%20Godavari%20region%20always%20referred%20to%20their%20spaces%20as%20%E2%80%98agency%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20outside%20world%20as%20%E2%80%98plain%20area%E2%80%99%2C%20from%20the%20long%20legacy%20of%20colonial%20configuration%20of%20their%20spaces%2C%20followed%20right%20through%20post-independence%20times%2C%20for%20better%20or%20for%20worse.%20%3Cem%3EIkkada%20%3C%2Fem%3E(home)%20was%20where%20things%20were%20simply%20accessed%20from%20the%20natural%20world%20around%2C%20while%20in%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20you%20%3Cem%3Ebought%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethings%20from%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152907%2Fimage-1237.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152907%2Fimage-1237.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152907%2Fimage-1237-300x132.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21152907%2Fimage-1237-1024x450.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668992%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22527%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20mother%20and%20daughter%20in%20Godavari.%20Photo%3A%20R.%20Umamaheshwari%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20home%20and%20village%20to%20R%26amp%3BR%20colony%3A%20what%20they%20said%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Madi%20Muttemma%20is%20living%20the%20life%20she%20was%20dreading%2C%20in%20the%20R%26amp%3BR%20colony%20(though%20not%20necessarily%20in%20the%20plain%20area%2C%20administratively%20speaking%2C%20yet%20%E2%80%98plain%E2%80%99%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20gradient%20and%20non-presence%20of%20hilly%20forests%20they%20were%20used%20to)%20in%20Neladonlapadu%2C%20near%20Gokavaram%2C%20approximately%2C%20they%20say%2C%2015%20kilometers%20from%20Rajahmundry%20town%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20When%20asked%20what%20had%20changed%20from%20%3Cem%3Ethere%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20%3Cem%3Ehere%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eshe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eikkada%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EGodavari%20ledandi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(there%20is%20no%20Godavari%20here).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20the%20past%2C%20where%20Godavari%20was%2C%20or%20came%20from%2C%20has%20been%20turned%20over.%20The%20same%20woman%20who%20spoke%20of%20the%20ideal%20world%2C%20her%20home%2C%20which%20was%20%3Cem%3Ehere%20%3C%2Fem%3Eso%20many%20years%20ago%20is%20now%20speaking%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Ehouse%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ehere%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20kind%20she%20feared.%20The%20intimate%20%3Cem%3Ehere%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20become%20the%20distant%20%3Cem%3Ethere%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20now%2C%20nostalgia%20is%20the%20only%20freedom%20available%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20Godavari%20and%20used%20to%20have%20free%20water%20for%20our%20needs%3B%20here%20they%20release%20water%20only%20once%20a%20day%20(sometimes%20it%20is%20every%20alternate%20day)%20for%20an%20hour%20and%20we%20have%20to%20fill%20our%20utensils%20for%20all%20our%20needs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intimacy%20of%20touching%20and%20feeling%20the%20river%20has%20ended.%20I%20remember%20the%20other%20image%20of%20the%20past%2C%20of%20a%20mother%20and%20daughter%20catching%20%3Cem%3Eseer%20meen%20%3C%2Fem%3E(tiny%20variety%20of%20fish%20that%20only%20comes%20around%20I%20summer%20months%20when%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20turbulence%20in%20the%20river)%20in%20their%20saree%20standing%20knee-deep%20in%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20coming%20here%2C%20it%20is%20indeed%20hard%20for%20us.%20As%20the%20day%20breaks%20here%2C%20we%20need%20to%20buy%20everything%2C%20even%20milk.%20We%20are%20not%20happy%20here%2C%20even%20though%20we%20have%20been%20here%20since%20a%20year%20now.%20It%20still%20feels%20new.%20We%20keep%20wondering%20why%20we%20came%20here%E2%80%A6%20No%20officer%20has%20come%20by%20to%20meet%20us%20after%20dumping%20us%20here.%20Many%20are%20yet%20to%20receive%20the%20complete%20R%26amp%3BR%20(package)%3B%20they%20have%20not%20given%20us%20the%20land%20they%20promised.%20Many%20are%20making%20ends%20meet%20by%20doing%20physical%20labour%20(%3Cem%3Ecoolie%20pani%3C%2Fem%3E)%20%E2%80%A6%20There%2C%20we%20grew%20our%20own%20food-crops%E2%80%A6%20There%20are%20no%20wild%20animals%20here%2C%20no%20wild%20boars%2C%20either.%20We%20have%20to%20buy%20meat%20from%20shops.%20But%20we%20do%20have%20our%20hens%20here.%20We%20had%20to%20sell%20away%20our%20cattle%20to%20traders%20before%20moving%20here%20because%20there%20is%20no%20place%20for%20them%20to%20graze%20here%E2%80%A6%20%C2%A0Tourist%20launches%20are%20still%20plying%20on%20Godavari%20from%20Polavaram%20to%20Perantapally%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202007%2C%20I%20had%20taken%20a%20boat%20ride%20and%20a%20long%20walk%20from%20Pochavaram%20to%20Kunavaram%20with%20Varada%20Kumari%20(of%20Kathanapally)%20and%20her%20spouse%20and%20we%20had%20waited%20at%203%20am%20on%20the%20sand%20beach%20of%20Godavari%20for%20the%20boat%20to%20arrive.%20Today%2C%20Varada%20Kumar%20introduced%20herself%20on%20the%20phone%2C%20saying%20%3Cem%3Ememu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EPolavaram%20nirvasitulam%20%3C%2Fem%3E(We%20are%20residents%20of%20Polavaram).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20put%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20difficulties%20there%20(in%20Kondamodalu)%20and%20were%20forced%20to%20move%20here%20without%20even%20getting%20the%20complete%20R%26amp%3BR.%20There%20is%20no%20Godavari%20here.%20There%20is%20no%20river%20at%20all.%20There%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekaluva%3C%2Fem%3E%20(canal)%20under%20Bhupatipalem%20project.%20They%20had%20promised%20they%20would%20give%20us%20426%20acres%20of%20land%20if%20we%20came%20here.%20They%20are%20yet%20to%20do%20so.%20We%20have%20no%20land%20right%20now%20to%20cultivate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20people%20now%20work%20for%20other%20farmers%2C%20the%20Kammas%20and%20Kapus.%20They%20pay%20us%20Rs%20300%20per%20day%20and%20we%20work%20from%209%20am%20till%204%20pm%E2%80%A6%20There%20%5Bin%20our%20previous%20homes%5D%20we%20had%20fish%20from%20Godavari%2C%20vegetables%2C%20tubers%2C%20etc.%20Here%20everything%20has%20to%20be%20purchased%2C%20including%20milk.%20None%20of%20us%20has%20cattle%20anymore.%20They%20gave%20us%20Rs%206%2C80%2C000%20as%20compensation%20per%20family.%20Those%20who%20could%20save%2C%20did%3B%20the%20rest%20have%20already%20spent%20it%20all%20on%20emergencies%20and%20so%20on%E2%80%A6There%20we%20had%20large%20homes.%20Here%20we%20are%20in%20two%20rooms%20and%20a%20kitchen%20in%20the%20verandah.%20We%20can%20no%20longer%20go%20hunting.%20There%20are%20no%20hills%20or%20forests%E2%80%A6Do%20you%20remember%20the%20house%20we%20slept%20in%20at%20Kathanapally%3F%20It%20is%20also%20under%20water%20now.%20These%20days%2C%20every%20time%20it%20rains%20our%20fields%20are%20inundated%2C%20unlike%20in%20the%20past.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBullebbayi%20of%20Kokkarigudem%20had%20in%202016%20walked%20me%2C%20literally%2C%20through%20the%20resistance%20history%20of%20Kondamodalu%2C%20showing%20me%20the%20martyrs%E2%80%99%20column%20that%20they%20constructed%20for%20those%20who%20died%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20land%20and%20forests%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20place%20cannot%20be%20compared%20to%20our%20village%20there%E2%80%A6%20We%20left%20everything%20back%20there%20and%20we%20are%20still%20perplexed%E2%80%A6%20I%20can%20foresee%20a%20very%20tough%20life%20ahead%20for%20%3Cem%3Egirijans%3C%2Fem%3E%20(adivasis).%20We%20fought%20for%20very%20long%20there.%20But%20the%20government%20snapped%20our%20electricity%20connections%20and%20many%20other%20facilities.%20In%20Kachuluru%20village%2C%20they%20broke%20down%20houses%2C%20too.%20They%20took%20away%20all%20the%20basic%20facilities%2C%20so%20even%20if%20one%20of%20us%20fell%20sick%2C%20it%20became%20very%20difficult%20to%20take%20the%20person%20to%20the%20hospital.%20We%20fought%20and%20remained%20there%2C%20despite%20all%20this%2C%20and%20demanded%20that%20we%20will%20move%20only%20if%20the%20government%20will%20give%20us%20what%20they%20promised.%20They%20fooled%20us%20saying%20if%20we%20went%20to%20the%20colony%2C%20we%20will%20get%20everything%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20him%2C%20what%20about%20all%20the%20history%20he%20had%20told%20me%20about%2C%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20struggle%20of%20our%20people%2C%20%3Cem%3Egirijans%3C%2Fem%3E%20(adivasis)%2C%20will%20have%20to%20continue%2C%20if%20our%20history%20has%20to%20remain.%20Today%2C%20numerous%20adivasis%20in%20our%20country%20are%20losing%20out%20to%20big%20projects%20and%20national%20parks%3B%20governments%20have%20taken%20over%20forests%2C%20too%2C%20from%20adivasis.%20Though%20our%20(country%E2%80%99s)%20president%20may%20be%20a%20%3Cem%3Egirijan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(adivasi)%2C%20yet%20there%20is%20no%20empathy%20towards%20them.%20We%20are%20still%20looked%20down%20upon.%20Even%20in%20Manipur%2C%20you%20can%20see%20how%20they%20are%20attacking%20%3Cem%3Egirijans%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Aren%E2%80%99t%20we%20seeing%20it%20all%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20being%20adivasi%20farmers%2C%20cultivating%20food%20crops%20for%20self-consumption%20on%20their%20own%20fields%2C%20they%20are%20now%20daily%20wage%20labourers%20for%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20landlords.%20Gone%20is%20the%20Sivagiri-Kondamodalu%20connect%2C%20gone%20are%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20boats%20and%20the%20boatmen%20and%20several%20villages%20that%20dotted%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVijaya%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CKondamodalu%20was%20totally%20ours.%20%3Cem%3ESvechchamga%20undevallam%3B%20ikkada%20svechcha%20ledu%20%3C%2Fem%3E(we%20used%20to%20live%20on%20our%20own%20terms%2C%20but%20here%2C%20autonomy%2Ffreedom%20does%20not%20exist).%20There%20no%20fields%20for%20cultivation.%20There%2C%20from%20the%20time%20we%20woke%20up%2C%20till%20we%20went%20to%20bed%2C%20the%20Godavari%2C%20the%20breeze%2C%20and%20water%20was%20all%20ours%3B%20here%20we%20have%20nothing.%20There%20is%20no%20water%20body%20either%2C%20barring%20one%20small%20channel%20for%20the%20fields%20of%20other%20farmers%E2%80%A6%20All%20our%20tamarind%20trees%2C%20toddy%20trees%20are%20there%E2%80%A6We%20used%20to%20get%20Kalapa%20to%20build%20our%20homes%20(from%20the%20forests)%20%E2%80%A6%20We%20used%20to%20get%20toddy%3B%20there%20are%20no%20toddy%20or%20%3Cem%3Eippa%20%3C%2Fem%3Etrees%20here.%20%3Cem%3EIkkada%20emi%20ledu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(There%20is%20nothing%20here)%20%E2%80%A6%20May%20be%20for%20education%2C%20it%20is%20alright%20since%20there%20are%20schools%20here%2C%20but%20children%20do%20not%20have%20the%20kind%20of%20lifestyle%20they%20had%20there%2C%20to%20play%20around%20in%20the%20open%20in%20a%20free%20environment%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20Vijaya%20says%20the%20%E2%80%98road%20to%20nowhere%E2%80%99%20to%20reach%20Kondamodalu%20(since%20there%20are%20no%20boats%20anymore)%20still%20exists%20(and%20that%20thankfully%20remains%20as%20a%20historic%20pathway%2C%20for%20nobody%20needs%20to%20walk%20down%20that%20road%20anymore)%2C%20so%20may%20be%20taking%20their%20invitation%20(warm%20as%20always%2C%20to%20partake%20of%20their%20food)%20one%20could%20walk%20down%20that%20pathway%20again%20in%20a%20future%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20home%20is%20a%20space%20%2F%20land%20elsewhere%20that%20they%20seek%20to%20make%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20others%2C%20it%20is%20a%20structure%20they%20are%20yet%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20as%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20it%20is%20%3Cem%3Ea%20%3C%2Fem%3Estructure%20(or%20several%20of%20them)%2C%20built%20in%20a%20fantasised%20elsewhere%20(or%20several%20elsewheres)%2C%20that%20money%20can%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20others%2C%20it%20is%20that%20place%20which%20money%20cannot%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20adivasis%20of%20Godavari%2C%20it%20will%20now%20forever%20remain%20%3Cem%3Eakkada%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20a%20valley%20that%20was%2C%20and%20never%20can%20be%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20many%20R%26amp%3BR%20colonies%20force%20them%20to%20accept%20it%2C%20%3Cem%3Eikkada%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20author%20is%20based%20in%20Shimla.%20Her%20recent%20(related)%20publication%20is%20titled%20%3C%2Fem%3ESpheres%20of%20Injustice%2C%20%3Cem%3Eedited%20by%20Albeena%20Shakil%2C%20Gopal%20Guru%2C%20(%3C%2Fem%3ERoutledge%20India%2C%202023.)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692617427000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F21153122%2Fimage-1239.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgodavari-isnt-here-from-intimacy-to-distance-for-the-adivasi-community%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20Godavari%20and%20used%20to%20have%20free%20water%20for%20our%20needs%3B%20here%20they%20release%20water%20only%20once%20a%20day%20for%20an%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20person%20from%20the%20adivasi%20community%20who%20was%20resettled%20from%20the%20ancestral%20land%20in%20rural%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgodavari-isnt-here-from-intimacy-to-distance-for-the-adivasi-community%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22San%20Francisco%20officials%20want%20to%20stop%20robotaxis%20operating%2024