azing%20how%20it%20takes%20the%20shape%20of%20a%20ball%20while%20there%20is%20no%20gravity.''%20Another%20commented%2C%20''What%20I'm%20seeing%20is%20that%20in%20space%20I%20can%20just%20leave%20my%20stuff%20anywhere%20and%20it's%20cool.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20joked%2C%20''eating%20in%20space%20would%20take%20me%20forever%E2%80%A6I%20would%20just%20be%20playing%20with%20my%20food.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20said%2C%20''The%20movement%20of%20things%20in%20space%20is%20influenced%20by%20gravity%20and%20the%20tendril-like%20behavior%20makes%20it%20look%20like%20it's%20alive.%20So%20amazing.''%20''Woah!%20That's%20fascinating%2C''%20added%20a%20fifth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20another%20clip%20of%20him%20surfaced%20wherein%20he%C2%A0had%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fadorable-video-shows-uae-astronaut-answering-his-sons-questions-from-space-4306528%5C%22%3Eadorable%20exchange%20with%20his%20son%3C%2Fa%3E%20via%20video%20conference.%20His%20son%C2%A0Abdulla%20Sultan%20Al%20Niyadi%20asked%20him%20what%20he%20liked%20best%20about%20Earth.%20''You%20are%20the%20thing%20that%20I%20love%20most%20about%20Earth%2C''%20Mr.%20Al%20Neyadi%20said%20while%20referring%20to%20his%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Emirati%20astronaut%20also%20shares%20beautiful%20pictures%20of%20Earth%20from%20space%2C%20which%20often%20go%20viral.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%2042-year-old%20astronaut%20and%20his%20four%20colleagues%20are%20set%20to%20begin%20their%20journey%20back%20to%20Earth%20on%20September%201%2C%20after%20completing%20a%20six-month%20science%20mission%20aboard%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20In%20April%20this%20year%2C%20Mr%20Neyadi%20became%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fuaes-sultan-al-neyadi-becomes-1st-arab-astronaut-to-complete-spacewalk-3989666%5C%22%3Efirst%20Arab%20to%20undertake%20a%20spacewalk%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eduring%20Expedition%2069%