_402_602.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20International%20Press%20Institute%20has%20welcomed%20the%20%E2%80%9Crepeal%20and%20replacement%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20draconian%20Digital%20Security%20Act%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20but%20called%20for%20consultation%20with%20civil%20society%20to%20ensure%20that%20proposed%20Cyber%20Security%20Act%20is%20compatible%20with%20international%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20its%20inception%20in%202018%2C%20the%20Digital%20Security%20Act%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20employed%20to%20target%20journalists%20and%20suppress%20dissent.%20The%20Vienna-based%20media%20watchdog%20had%20highlighted%20that%20at%20least%20nine%20journalists%20faced%20complaints%20under%20the%20DSA%20between%20October%202022%20and%20March%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20Bangladeshi%20government%20responded%20to%20widespread%20concerns%20and%20announced%20its%20intention%20to%20replace%20the%20Digital%20Security%20Act%20with%20the%20Cyber%20Security%20Act.%20The%20replacement%20entails%20the%20repeal%20or%20amendment%20of%20existing%20DSA%20provisions%2C%20along%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20new%20penalties%20for%20hacking-related%20offences.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%207%2C%20a%20cabinet%20meeting%20presided%20over%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20granted%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailystar.net%2Fnews%2Fbangladesh%2Fnews%2Fcyber-security-act-replace-dsa-3388841%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ein-principle%20approval%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20draft%20Cyber%20Security%20Act.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20IPI%20global%20network%20welcomes%20the%20recent%20decision%20by%20the%20Bangladeshi%20government%20to%20repeal%20and%20replace%20the%20Digital%20Security%20Act%2C%20which%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20abused%20for%20years%20to%20harass%20and%20intimidate%20journalists.%20However%2C%20authorities%20must%20now%20consult%20with%20local%20civil%20society%20and%20human%20rights%20experts%20to%20ensure%20the%20proposed%20replacement%2C%20the%20Cyber%20Security%20Act%2C%20is%20fully%20compatible%20with%20domestic%20and%20international%20laws%20protecting%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20access%20to%20information%2C%20and%20press%20freedom%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fipi.media%2Fbangladesh-ipi-welcomes-repeal-and-replacement-of-digital-security-act%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%20IPI%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20this%20year%20in%20May%2C%20IPI%20sent%20an%20open%20letter%20to%20PM%20Hasina%20urging%20her%20government%20to%20review%20the%20DSA%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20journalists%20can%20work%20without%20fear%20of%20intimidation%20and%20harassment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20recent%20invocations%20of%20DSA%20was%20in%20July%20when%20a%20private%20complaint%20was%20registered%20against%20two%20journalists%2C%20when%20they%20accidentally%20published%20a%20report%20about%20the%20resignation%20of%20Cambodia%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20with%20a%20photo%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20PM.%20The%20newspaper%20had%20apologised%20the%20very%20next%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20welcoming%20the%20Bangladesh%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20replace%20the%20DSA%2C%20IPI%E2%80%99s%20head%20of%20advocacy%20Amy%20Brouillette%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20government%20must%20now%20work%20with%20a%20range%20of%20stakeholders%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Cyber%20Security%20Act%20abides%20by%20national%20and%20international%20commitments%20to%20press%20freedom%20and%20does%20not%20revive%20the%20problematic%20provisions%20of%20the%20DSA%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20reiterated%20that%20Bangladesh%